               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-213-person1596">
                  RICHARD 
                  RINGER
               <interp inst="t18310630-213-person1596" type="surname" value="RINGER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-213-person1596" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-213-person1596" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in <placeName id="t18310630-213-crimeloc1119">Lower Dorchester-street, Connaught-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-213-crimeloc1119" type="placeName" value="Lower Dorchester-street, Connaught-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-213-crimeloc1119" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-213-off1117 t18310630-213-crimeloc1119"></join>. I lost a watch on the 9th of June, from a mantel-piece in my parlour, adjoining my shop - I had seen the prisoner there twice that day; I afterwards saw him in the Heart of Oak tavern - I asked him for the watch; he took it from his pocket, and endeavoured to pass it to another person or persons in his company - he had been employed by me as a carpenter, and had access to that room; I taxed him with it a day or two after I missed it, and asked if he had not taken it in a lark or joke - he denied it; I asked a man named Finch if he had it, and he said No, he had returned it to Wilks.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BALL. Q. What are you? -A. A green-grocer - I have known the prisoner five months; I did treat this as a lark - Finch is no friend of mine; I did not see any fun going on when I found it - I asked Finch, (whose name I did not know at that time,) to show me the watch he received from Wilks, and he said he had returned it to him; I then asked Wilks for it - he denied it, but he took it out, and was handing it to the other - I said if he did not give it up I would get an officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-213-person1597">
                  SOPHIA 
                  RINGER
               <interp inst="t18310630-213-person1597" type="surname" value="RINGER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-213-person1597" type="given" value="SOPHIA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-213-person1597" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prosecutor's wife. In the month of May the prisoner was at our house - my husband's watch hung on a nail over the mantel-piece; I missed it between ten and eleven o'clock at night - this is it - it is worth 40s.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-213-person1598">
